At Flix, we offer a dynamic work environment with competitive pay, strong growth opportunities, and a tech-driven approach to making travel more accessible, sustainable, and affordable. &nbsp;
As a Senior Data Analyst (m/f/d), you will be a part of the Commercial Intelligence Team within our Commercial Analytics unit. You will be responsible for strengthening our analytics capabilities and directly impacting the company's success. In this highly visible role, you will drive the development of analytical products and standards that enable data‑driven pricing, marketing, and revenue decisions across the organization. Working closely with Revenue Management and Commercial Excellence, and Marketing stakeholders, you will translate complex data into actionable insights and scalable, automated solutions that support profitable and sustainable growth.
About the Role


Proven experience building, maintaining, and optimizing reporting solutions in Power BI and Excel
Ability to proactively identify new reporting needs and improve existing analytical processes with business stakeholders
Hands-on, autonomous, and well‑organized working style suited for a highly visible, impact‑driven role
Experience translating business questions into insights and clearly communicating findings to non‑technical audiences
Solid documentation skills to ensure accuracy and transparency of data products and reports
Strong analytical mindset with the ability to support revenue optimization processes, profitability, and sustainable growth

Contribute to advancing the&nbsp;know-how&nbsp;and&nbsp;skill-set&nbsp;within the team through sharing knowledge and best&nbsp;practice



About You


5+ years of professional experience as a Data Analyst or Business Analyst
Strong SQL skills and hands‑on experience working with Snowflake. Python, Power Platform, Jenkins/GitLab, and VS Code experience is considered an advantage
Solid experience in building analytical models and reports using Power BI (connected to Snowflake)
Advanced Microsoft Excel skills, including complex formulas and macros. Experience with AI tools will be considered an advantage&nbsp;
Experience working in Agile team environments, ideally alongside other analysts
Proven ability to communicate insights effectively to internal and external non‑technical stakeholders
Fluent English (spoken and written)


We recognize that everyone carries a unique set of valuable skills and experiences. If you think you could have an impact even though you don't meet 100% of the requirements, we still encourage you to apply. We want to hear from you! &nbsp;
What We Offer

Travel perks: 12 free Flix vouchers + 12 discount vouchers for friends &amp; family.&nbsp;
Work from (M)Anywhere: Depending on your role, work from another location for up to 60 days per year.&nbsp;
Hybrid work model: We are an office-first company, but we offer flexibility to balance work and life.&nbsp;
Wellbeing support: Access confidential 1:1 counselling, courses, and stress management for yourself and up to four family members.&nbsp;
Learning &amp; Development: Take advantage of language classes, training courses, and expert-led sessions to grow your skills.&nbsp;
Mentoring Program: Connect with experienced colleagues to gain insights and accelerate your career.&nbsp;

To view more local benefits specific to each office location, please check out this link:&nbsp;Locations - Flix Career

Why Join Flix?
At Flix, you'll find teams that rally together to overcome challenges and spark creativity. We believe in ownership culture - giving you the freedom to take initiative, make an impact, and shape your own career path.As we continue to expand across the globe, you can make a real difference in how we work.
If you're ready to grow and lead your journey, Flix is the place for you!&nbsp;

